==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumvention
<hw>Cir`cum*ven"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumventio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of prevailing over another
by arts, address, or fraud; deception; fraud; imposture;
delusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A school in which he learns sly <qex>circumvention</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumventive</ent>⟦br⟧
